        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 5:19PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 518 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dryden, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dryden and Terrell County Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
